Here's how to add server-side processing to save form data using PHP and Node.js:

**PHP Example:**

```php
<?php
if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {
  // Collect form data
  $name = $_POST["name"];
  $email = $_POST["email"];
  $message = $_POST["message"];

  // Validate data (add your own validation rules)
  if (empty($name) || empty($email) || empty($message)) {
    echo "Please fill in all fields.";
    exit;
  }

  // Save data to a database or file
  // Example using a simple file:
  $file = fopen("form_data.txt", "a");
  fwrite($file, "Name: $name\nEmail: $email\nMessage: $message\n\n");
  fclose($file);

  echo "Form submitted successfully!";
}
?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

  <h1>Contact Us</h1>

  <form action="<?php echo htmlspecialchars($_SERVER["PHP_SELF"]); ?>" method="post"> 
    <label for="name">Name:</label>
    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required><br><br>

    <label for="email">Email:</label>
    <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required><br><br>

    <label for="message">Message:</label>
    <textarea id="message" name="message" rows="4" cols="50"></textarea><br><br>

    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
  </form>

</body>
</html>
```

**Node.js Example (using Express):**

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();

app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: true }));

app.post('/submit-form', (req, res) => {
  const name = req.body.name;
  const email = req.body.email;
  const message = req.body.message;

  // Validate data (add your own validation rules)
  if (!name || !email || !message) {
    return res.status(400).send('Please fill in all fields.');
  }

  // Save data to a database or file
  // Example using a simple file (replace with your database logic):
  const fs = require('fs');
  fs.appendFile('form_data.txt', `Name: ${name}\nEmail: ${email}\nMessage: ${message}\n\n`, err => {
    if (err) {
      console.error(err);
      return res.status(500).send('Error saving data.');
    }
    res.send('Form submitted successfully!');
  });
});

app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log('Server listening on port 3000');
});
```

**Key Points:**

- **Server-Side Language:** Choose a language like PHP, Node.js, Python, etc., based on your preference and project requirements.
- **Form Handling:** Use the appropriate methods to access form data (e.g., `$_POST` in PHP, `req.body` in Node.js).
- **Validation:** Implement validation to ensure data integrity and prevent errors.
- **Data Storage:** Choose a suitable method for storing the data (database, file, etc.).
- **Response:** Send a response back to the client (e.g., success message, error message, redirection).
